
The bully rolled and eyes before darting them at Erik, then he turned and walked out.
"And Curt... Please go to the guidance counselor," Taylor said as softly as possible. She knew he was damaged and she strongly believed he did need mental help.
As if it was a routine, the miserable child got up and walked out, without a struggle. After, the whole class looked at Erik as he slowly got up and sat in his seat.
The teacher returned to the board she used often, stained in certain parts with marker. As she started blabbering, Erik could only worry about the man he barely knew.